{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create your first macOS virtual machine in minutes."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Spooktacular runs macOS virtual machines on Apple Silicon using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s Virtualization framework. You interact with it through the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"GUI app or the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"type":"text","text":" CLI — both backed by the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"},{"type":"text","text":" library. A Kubernetes operator is planned for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a future release."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Important","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You need an Apple Silicon Mac (M1 or later) running"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"macOS 14.0 (Sonoma) or later. Each VM requires at least 20 GB of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"free disk space and 4 CPU cores (see"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VirtualMachineSpecification\/minimumCPUCount"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]}],"style":"important"},{"anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-CLI","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Creating a VM with the CLI"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Install Spooktacular and create a VM from the latest compatible IPSW:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["# Install via Homebrew","brew install --cask spooktacular","","# Create from the latest compatible IPSW","spook create my-vm --from-ipsw latest","","# Or specify custom hardware resources","spook create runner --cpu 8 --memory 16 --disk 100"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"IPSW installation takes 10–20 minutes per VM. For faster"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"deployment, create a base VM once, then use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook clone"},{"type":"text","text":" for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instant copies."}]}],"style":"note"},{"anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-GUI","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Creating a VM with the GUI"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Open Spooktacular."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Click the "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"+","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" button or press "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cmd+N","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Enter a name and adjust hardware settings."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Click "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Create","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The app downloads the latest compatible macOS IPSW and installs it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"into a new VM bundle."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Managing-VMs","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Managing VMs"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"type":"text","text":" CLI for day-to-day VM management:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["# List all VMs","spook list","","# Start a VM (opens display window)","spook start my-vm","","# Start headless (for CI runners and servers)","spook start my-vm --headless","","# Clone instantly using APFS copy-on-write","spook clone my-vm runner-01","","# Show VM configuration","spook get my-vm","","# Delete a VM permanently","spook delete my-vm --force"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"name":"Important","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple Silicon supports a maximum of 2 concurrent VMs"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"per host. Attempting to start a third VM fails. See"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CapacityCheck"},{"type":"text","text":" for details."}]}],"style":"important"},{"anchor":"Provisioning-with-User-Data-Scripts","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Provisioning with User-Data Scripts"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Automate VM setup by running a shell script after boot via SSH:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["spook start runner --headless \\","    --user-data ~\/setup.sh \\","    --provision ssh \\","    --ssh-user admin"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ssh"},{"type":"text","text":" mode waits for the VM to boot, discovers its IP, connects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"via SSH, and executes your script with real-time output streaming."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Disk-inject provisioning (zero-touch, no SSH required) is in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"progress. See "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProvisioningMode"},{"type":"text","text":" for provisioning strategies and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"doc:Provisioning"},{"type":"text","text":" for detailed guidance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"EC2-Mac-Setup","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"EC2 Mac Setup"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Deploy Spooktacular on AWS EC2 Mac instances to double your CI"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"capacity. Install Spooktacular, create VMs from IPSW, clone"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"configured bases, and start runners with SSH provisioning."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment"},{"type":"text","text":" for detailed EC2 Mac configuration."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A Kubernetes operator (MacOSVM CRD) is planned for a future"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"release. See "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide"},{"type":"text","text":" for the planned architecture."}]}],"style":"note"}]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/JenkinsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Guides","title":"Guides"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/gettingstarted"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"title":"Getting Started with Spooktacular","role":"collectionGroup"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentati